{"TopicId":161428,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"KLAW-S2","CreatedByName":"Casualnaut","CreatedById":178396,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-01T20:39:20Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Casualnaut","CreatedById":178396,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-01T20:39:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Trebuchet MS\u0027, Helvetica, sans-serif;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003EThis is my first suggestion, and it has to do with probes collecting surface samples. I suggest you make the KLAW-S2 as a rover arm that has a science operation similar to a surface sample. For example, collecting a sample of Minimus would be:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Trebuchet MS\u0027, Helvetica, sans-serif;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cem\u003E\u0022The material is frozen and fluffy, probably would make good snow cones.\u0022\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Trebuchet MS\u0027, Helvetica, sans-serif;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003EWhat it looks like? Well sort of like this:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Image result for rover arm\u0022 class=\u0022ipsAttachLink_image ipsAttachLink_left\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.hcastano.com/assets/img/portfolio/RyArm2.jpg\u0022 style=\u0022width:684px;height:auto;float:left;\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003ET\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Trebuchet MS\u0027, Helvetica, sans-serif;\u0022\u003Ehis would be it\u0027s product description.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Trebuchet MS\u0027, Helvetica, sans-serif;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cem\u003E\u0022After years of playing at an arcade claw machine, we have finally made the best grabbing machine ever! Warranty void if it actually is from a claw machine.\u0022\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"qzgy","CreatedById":160994,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-02T05:08:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn general, a canada arm like thing could be cool. Actually also really useful.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis seems more like a small surface experiment. I guess that\u0027s what you are proposing, right?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Skylon","CreatedById":175317,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-02T07:57:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGood idea! Not sure why we don\u0027t have a robot arm, maybe it just woudnt be structurally sound\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey could also add a science experiment to the the drills\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-06-02T07:58:00Z\u0022 title=\u002206/02/2017 07:58  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJune 2, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Skylon\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NSEP","CreatedById":165635,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-02T08:34:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI always wanted unmanned surface sample return missions in KSP. So yeah! Great idea!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Casualnaut","CreatedById":178396,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-02T17:31:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223077155\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161428\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496380107\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022160994\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022qzgy\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 hours ago, qzgy said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn general, a canada arm like thing could be cool. Actually also really useful.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis seems more like a small surface experiment. I guess that\u0027s what you are proposing, right?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, that is what I was proposing. All though I now think about it, the KLAW S-2 can be multi-purpose. You can have it be a science experiment when on a surface, but can be extended and armed in all environments!\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-03T06:09:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt could extend in the same manner as drills. The only thing a player should do is to ensure that the instrument can reach ground. No need for additional movements, hinges, servos etc.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jas0n","CreatedById":57441,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-09T02:33:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy is my first reaction to the picture let\u0027s make a crab probe.......\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso cool idea now I don\u0027t have to strand a kerbal to get a surface sample.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-09T03:06:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223085465\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161428\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496975632\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257441\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jas0n\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n31 minutes ago, Jas0n said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy is my first reaction to the picture let\u0027s make a crab probe.......\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso cool idea now I don\u0027t have to strand a kerbal to get a surface sample.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell that would make Kerbals even more useless. Why even bother with manned missions then?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Skylon","CreatedById":175317,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-09T06:06:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223085495\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161428\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496977613\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150811\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Aziz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, The Aziz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell that would make Kerbals even more useless. Why even bother with manned missions then?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe we could have a higher science return for kerbals\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}